instance: A fine, pedantic sunshine in a satin waistcoat
A blunt head in the middle of windy rooms.
A silence pervades the story, and a gentleness the eye of the narrator
And the storm must hurt
But pale and thin due to the water The innocent feet are still shining
Every street lamp I pass Beats like a fatalistic drum
Hope is the thing with feathers that sits in the soul and sings the melody without words and never stops
I do not detract from the beauty of being mute
I heard it in the coldest country
The heart of the ocean too smooth, too blue
The reminiscence comes From sunless dry geraniums
The yellow mist that rubs its back against the window panes
The yellow smoke that rubs its snout against the window panes
Under a windy knob.
Where the troubled bodies of the drowned float in the green silence
a crow flying in the sweetest air of the sky
the face of a woman painted with the hand of nature
like the sweet shivers on the floor
and hide your bravery in their foul smoke
silenced the shrunken seas
kisses the green meadows with a golden face
the beauty of my sweet love
sometimes too hot the eye of the sky shines
that sweet smell
the bottoms of the still seas.
the sessions of sweet silent thoughts
the wide world and all its fading sweets
their substance still lives sweetly
Listening with the eyes is part of the fine mind of love
to give your sweet glow to another
